<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-755-680  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 755 680.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  May 29 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New Jersey Bell to offer voice messaging service to residences.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   New Jersey Bell Telephone Co. (services).andO;Topic:     Voice MailMarket EntryCommunications Service Suppliers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW JERSEY BELL TO OFFER VOICE MESSAGING SERVICE TO RESIDENCES NEWARK, NEWJERSEY, U.S.A., MAY 22 (NB) -- New Jersey Bell, the Bell Atlantic phonecompany which leads in the implementation of the controversial Caller IDservice, announced plans to roll out a voice messaging service.andM;First tested in 1989 with customers in Plainfield, Answer Call cuts down ontelephone tag by allowing callers to leave messages if a number is busy orgoes unanswered.andP;  Each member of a household can have a &quot;voice mailbox&quot; andrecord a personalized greeting for callers.andP;  Answer Call customers can electto have up to eight personalized mailboxes per household, and 2 messagestorage options.andP;  Prices range from $5-8 per month.andP;  A one-time connectioncharge of $21 associated with the service will be waived from May 30-August27.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900525/Press Contact: New Jersey Bell, Karen A. Johnson,201/649-2282)</TEXT></DOC>